
[1]inconveniency

   INCONVE'NIENCY, n. [L.inconveniens; in and convenio, conveniens.]

   1. Unfitness; unsuitableness; inexpedience.

   They plead against the inconvenience, not the unlawfulness of popish
   apparel.

   2. That which gives trouble or uneasiness; disadvantage; any thing that
   disturbs quiet, impedes prosperity, or increases the difficulty of
   action or success. Rain and bad roads are inconveniences to the
   traveler; want of utensils is a great inconvenience to a family; but
   the great inconvenience of human life is the want of money and the
   means of obtaining it.
